                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 11: State-run oil companies are losing Rs 170 crore per day by selling auto fuel and cooking gas below cost. However, the government has no plans to hike fuel prices even as global crude is trading around $71 a barrel. Global prices are not comfortable. But there is no immediate proposal to revise the price, petroleum secretary R.S. Pandey said.                            
	 Chennai, Sept. 11: IT minister A. Raja today indicated that software firms might be given tax exemption for three more years from 2011. The proposal is awaiting cabinet approval.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 11: The RBI today directed banks to maintain records of all customers right from the date of transaction for a period of 10 years to help track funds used in illegal activities.                            
